The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | PCA criticises ICC plan
                                                                                                                       7                                      PCA criticises ICC plan
                      
	London: After Australia, the Professional Cricketers Association (PCA) has also cast doubts on the viability of having undercover agents posing as illegal bookmakers to nab corrupt players, saying it is hard to see the International Cricket Councils (ICC) plan being a serious runner.         
	I suspect its a case of ICC throwing out an idea which was intended to demonstrate theyre considering everything, rather than a fully thought-through proposal. Its hard to see it being a serious runner, PCA CEO Angus Porter was quoted as saying by an English daily.           (PTI)                                                                                                                 
